-- Fifth-Seeded Andy Roddick Upset by Yen-Hsun Lu in Wimbledon Fourth Round
-- James Cone
-- 2010-06-28T18:58:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/fifth-seeded-andy-roddick-upset-by-yen-hsun-lu-in-wimbledon-fourth-round.html

          
          
             Three-time runner-up Andy Roddick
was upset by Yen-Hsun Lu in a five set match today in the fourth
round of the Wimbledon tennis championship.  
 Taiwan’s Lu, who lost in the first round the past four
years at the All England Club in southwest London, defeated No.
5 seed Roddick of the U.S. 4-6, 7-6 (7-3), 7-6 (7-4), 6-7 (5-7),
9-7.  
 Lu will play Serbia’s Novak Djokovic in the next round.  
          
          


  


        